@node "What's" "What's a REMINDER?"

   WHAT'S A MReminder?

    MReminder is a very simple program made to help you to remind (that's
incredible!) appointments, birthdays, important days or other, like when to
do a back-up or so on!

    Using Mreminder every time you turn your Amiga on, you'll be able to
know that today it's your girlfriend's birthday, or that you have to bring
the dog out becouse the last day your wife did it.

    Stupid and little things, but forgetting them, you could be loose!
@endnode

@node "Install" "Install MReminder"

  INSTALLING

Installing MReminder is very easy, even if there isn't any installation
script.

1) Copy MReminder in WBStartup drawer of your Workbench.

2) Copy MReminderGUI in Prefs drawer of your Workbench or wherever
   you prefer.

That's all!!



  REQUIREMENTS

MReminder needs:

  - Amiga (of course!!)

  - 020 or better CPU

  - reqtools.library


...and nothing else!!


  IMPORTANT
  ---------

   If you upgrade from a previous version of MReminder, you cannot use the
same files of configuration, but you need to create new ones. I'm sorry for
this, but I had to. Anyway, if even just one asks me, I'll make a converter
from the old to the new format for the configuration.
@endnode

@node "MReminderGUI" "MReminderGUI"

  MREMINDER GUI

    This is the first of two programs. This is used just to set the thing to
be reminded! It's easy to use, so you don't have to care about any config.


ADD      This is used to add a new record to the list. You have to set
         what kind of record you want before clicking on it choosing from
         the list on the left side of the window.

EDIT     This is used to edit a previously saved record. You have to select
         which one by the listview below before clicking on this gadget.

DELETE   This is used to delete the record marked in the listview below. A
         deleted record cannot be recovered, so use it carefully.

CALENDAR Clicking here, a new window pops up showing all the items of the
         current month. You can also browse to other months or year. In
         this way you can see all things you must do in the month at the
         beginning or you can see if you have anything important in the
         next days when you go on holiday and so on.
         Daily messages are not shown, of course!
         BEWARE: The coloumn on the left in Monday and the one on the
         right is Sunday: this is how calendar works in Italy even if I
         know it isn't the same everywhere.

EASTER   Clicking on this gadget, a new window pops up: you can decide
         if you want a message in the day of Easter and type the Easter
         message. On the top side of the window you can see the Easter
         date starting from 1900 up to 2099. Just one more utility!

SELF CLEAN   When this function is active, MReminder tries to clean the
             record list by itself, eliminating all past events since it's
             impossible they are used again. This means it works only on
             Event and InXday messages.

ONCE A DAY   When this function is active, MReminder shows the messages
             just once a day (!) and quits all other times. Very useful
             to avoid reading all the same messages every time you boot!


MENUS... Nothing important, just try them!!


There are 7 different kinds of messages:

1) EVENT    You must say the day, the month and the year and the message
            is displayed just in that day. If you use Events and want to
            delete them automatically, turn Self Clean on.

2) BIRTHDAY Very useful to remind you birthdays since it allow you to enter
            the year when a person was born. Using # in the text lines of
            the message, they are automatically replaced by the age. Fx:
            Today Mike is # years old!

3) YEARLY   This kind of messages are shown every year in the same day.
            Very useful for all the anniversaries.

4) MONTHLY  MReminder shows these messages every month.

5) WEEKLY   You must enter the day of the week you want to see the message;
            in these kind of messages anticipation can be just 1 or 0.
            (read below for anticipation)

6) DAYLY    MReminder shows these messages every day! No anticipation is
            possible... of course!!!

7) EVERY X  MReminder shows these messages Every X days, starting from the
            date you add or edit each of them. Anticipation cannot be
            higher than X (read below for anticipation). Very useful for
            remembering backups or to call your mother!!!

8) Nth DAY  It is used to show messages on the first monday, on the third
            thursday, on the last sunday and so on of each month. It can
            be very useful.

9) IN X DAY This is one of my favourite kind of messages: please, come
            back in 10 days. And MReminder is my only chance to be there
            after 10 days!!



ANTICIPATION: Anticipation is an useful feature of MReminder: it allows you
to display messages also before the right day, printing in the message:
   "In X days:"   where X is how far the right day is. Anticipation is very
useful if you don't turn your Amiga on every day, so you don't risk to miss
a message or if you want to know about an anniversary some days before to
send a card. Usually Anticipation can range from 0 (no anticipation) up to
9; daily messages cannot have anticipation (of course) and weekly messages
can have just 1 day anticipation. When a message with anticipation is shown,
MReminder gives you the ability to leave anticipation: this mean that the
message will be shown again just in the right day. By the way, as soon as
the day is past, the anticipation is restored to its original value
automatically.
@endnode

@node "MReminder" "MReminder"

  MREMINDER

This is the second program. How do you use it? Just copy it to the WBStartup
drawer of your Workbench. In this way the program is activated avery time
you boot.

If MReminder has to remind you something, it displays a message. You can
choose between three options:

Continue            will go on, checking if there are other messages to be
                    shown or, otherwise, quitting.

Leave Anticipation: will switch the anticipation of that message off. This
                    means that all the other messages will continue having
                    their own anticipation value. Moreover the message will
                    be displayed in the right day even if the anticipation
                    is off and then the anticipation will be restored to
                    its original status.

Delete              will delete the shown message so you won't see it
                    again. For example, let's pretend a weekly message
                    like: Call your sister. Then, unluckly, she comes to
                    your house, so you can delete it (or her?)
@endnode

@node "History" "History"

 HISTORY

 - v3.1 :  MReminder is totally rewritten in ASM
           Over 20 times smaller and much much faster!!

 - v3.0 :  Internal version... working on faster routines

 - v2.2 :  Removed a little bug.
           Speed much improved using memory in a better way.
           Rewritten most of code.
           New icon for MReminder program.

 - v2.1 :  Added two new types of items (In X days and Nth day).
           Added Calendar.
           Eliminated a bug in empty lists of items.
           (internal version)

 - v2.0 :  Program totally rewritten.
           New Gui.
           Added Auto-clean and Once_a_day abilities.
           Added Easter ability.
           Added Birthday type.
           Added anticipation value for each message.
           (released only on local bbs)

 - v1.1 :  Corrected several bugs.

 - v1.0 :  Very first release.
@endnode

